oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Uniform breeches with web belt
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: These issue uniform breeches with web belt, button fly, with reinforced legs and laced closures belonged to John William Cato. The contractor's label on inside left pocket reads "Sol. Newman / 24 E. 14th St., New York /Contract October 22, 1917 / spec. no. 1263 amended / New York Depot, Q.M.C."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
